name: CBN Capsules
description: CBN or Cannabinol is the primary sedative componant found in cannabis, as well as being an extremely useful cannabinoid for musculoskeletal pain. A degradation byproduct of THC, its high affinity for CB2 receptors makes this unique product very useful as a supplement for a myriad of conditions.

name: GG#4 – RSO
description: RSO’s simply refer to decarboxylated cannabis oils that were intended for sublingual delivery. The term acknowledges the role of Rick Simpson in bringing attention to this methodology, though today many of his beliefs and practices need to be taken w/ a grain of salt.

name: “Sativa” Gel Pen – THC
description:
These transdermal Gel Pens work very similarly

to the patches. The gel “matrix” works by penetrating

the stratum corneum, into the dermis, and thereby

entering the bloodstream. These gels are different from

other “Topical” applications, which work only on the

very surface of the skin.

name: Patch – Sativa
description: Transdermal patches are particularly useful for those who require small doses. Patches allow for the slow diffusion of cannabinoids into the blood stream, which in turn can provide long lasting relief, while mitigating psychoactivity.

description:
Unlike the other Mary’s Medicinals products, this

Topical “Compound” is not a transdermal product, but
